  "doc_id": "41264",
  "text": "Promoters were first clustered into those sharing a common scaffold, using Bowtie2 to align to the known scaffold sequences (using the following parameters: -L 18 -p 4 -f --nosq --no-head --np 0 --n-ceil C,100). Promoters were then sub-clustered within each scaffold using the sequences of the random 80-mers using CD-HIT (version 4.6.5, using the following parameters: -g 1 -p 1 -r 0 -c 0.96 -uS 0.05 -uL 0.05 -mismatch -1) [CITATION_1] , yielding a single consensus sequence for each promoter.",
